sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641036
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a complete invertase-EGFP expressing device induced by arabinose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Pai Li
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This brick is constructed through cut-and-link of other bricks without risky sources, usually E. coli originated genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
All invertase generators are constructed as following structure:
AraC+Pbad::RBS::invertase-EGFP(-ssra)::terminator

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Fusion protein of Cre::EGFP::ssra-tag, with RBS at beginning
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a sequence of RBS (BBa_B0034) followed by a fusion protein of Cre::EGFP::ssra-tag.
Cre is a most commonly used recombinase with invertase activity that turns the sequence between two anti-parallel LoxP sites up-side-down. A EGFP fusion at the C-term of Cre has been proved by us not to significantly interfere the enzymatic activity. A ssra-tag (BBa_M0051) can accelerate the degradation of the protein, in order to clean it up when not in need.
This part is for expression of Cre::EGFP::ssra-tag, which aims to overturn our invertase modules in our Micro-timer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Pai Li
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Cre from BBa_K1179058 and EGFP::ssra-tag from pBI121-EGFP is fused by overlap-PCR; others through connection of bricks.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Ssra-Tag is efficiently cleaning the protein when not under induction, and helps to reduce leakage expression. C-term EGFP fusion on Cre work pretty good for activity, which we proved.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Artificial terminator, estimated %T~>90% *8bp stem, 6nt loop *Bidirectional, estimated reverse %T~>90%
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 9 residues.
